Title : Party for Democracy and Progress (Mali)
Text : {{Politics of Mali}}

The '''Party for Democracy and Progress''' ({{lang-fr|Parti pour la Démocratie et le Progrès}}, PDP) is a political party in [[Mali]] led by [[Mady Konaté]].

==History==
The party was established in 1991,<ref>''Africa South of the Sahara 2003'' Psychology Press, p652</ref> and officially registered on 25 April that year.<ref>[http://www.izf.net/sites/default/files/EE_Partis%20Politiques_19_09_2012.pdf Directory of Political Parties] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502214724/http://www.izf.net/sites/default/files/EE_Partis%20Politiques_19_09_2012.pdf |date=2014-05-02 }} Ministry of the Interior</ref> It party received 5.1% of the vote in the [[Malian parliamentary election, 1992|February 1992 parliamentary elections]], winning two seats. In the [[Malian presidential election, 1992|April 1992 presidential elections]] it nominated [[Idrissa Traoré (politician)|Idrissa Traoré]] as its candidate. Traoré finished fifth out of nine candidates with 7.1%^ of the vote.<ref name=AED>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/ml.html Elections in Mali] African Elections Database</ref> The local elections in the same year saw the party win 40 of the 751 seats across the country.<ref name=SW>Susanna D. Wing (2008) ''Constructing Democracy in Transitioning Societies of Africa: Constitutionalism and Deliberation in Mali'', Palgrave Macmillan, p92</ref>

Traoré was the party's candidate again in the [[Malian presidential election, 1997|1997 presidential elections]], but his vote share was reduced to 1.2%. The party retained its two seats in the [[Malian parliamentary election, July 1997|parliamentary elections]], running in alliance with [[Alliance for Democracy in Mali|ADEMA]]. In the local elections held in 1998–99 the party won 96 of the 10,545 seats available.<ref name=SW/> The [[Malian presidential election, 2002|2002 presidential elections]] saw the party nominate [[Mady Konaté]] as its candidate, but he received just 0.7% of the vote.<ref name=AED/>

The party did not contest the [[Malian parliamentary election, 2013|2013 parliamentary elections]].<ref>[http://www.matcl.gov.ml/PDF/SITUAT_PARTICI_PP_LEGISL2013.pdf Participation status of political parties in the 2013 legislative elections] Ministry of the Interior</ref>

